Popular actor, Lateef Adedimeji has described himself as the king of biopics as he plays the role of the president-elect, Bola Ahmed Tinubu in a new movie. Titled ‘Jagaban: Last Man Standing’, the movie is produced by Ultimate Communication. It stars the likes of Gbenga Adeyinka, Boy George, Madam Kofo, and Shushu Abubakar who plays Remi Tinubu among others. “At this point, please feel free to call me the king of biopics. From ‘Ayinla’ to ‘Ige’ (unlikely oil merchant) to ‘Strangers’ to ‘Jagaban: Last Man Standing’. Dear @officialasiwajubat, It was an honour relaying your remarkable story in the movie, ‘Jagaban: Last Man Standing’. “As we prepare to premiere the movie in May 2023, we take the opportunity to wish you a peaceful and successful time in office as the 16th President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. Happy Birthday sir. God’s wisdom and mercies remain with you now and always,” he wrote on Instagram. In 2021, the actor starred as the lead character in ‘Ayinla’, a musical eponymous film based on the life of Ayinla Yusuf popularly known as Ayinla Omowura, an Apala musician who was stabbed to death by his manager named Bayewu in a bar fight on 6 May 1980 at Abeokuta. Directed by Tunde Kelani, the film was set in the 1970s and early 1980s and shot in Abeokuta, Ogun State. Lateef Adedimeji assumed the role of Ayinla, starring alongside Omowumi Dada, Bimbo Manuel, Ade Laoye, Kunle Afolayan, Bimbo Ademoye and Mr Macaroni. ‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒